> Hello all, I'm trying to set up a brand new 1600cc dual port motor running a
> new 34PICT-3 carb and can't get it to idle. Timing is set 32 degrees total
> advance on a 009 distributor. It runs great above about 2500 rpms, but
> stumbles and dies when it approaches idle. The throttle positioner screw has
> to be on the topmost notch just to stay running. I saw a video on YouTube that
> recommends 2 1/2 turns out on both the volume and mixture screws, but this
> leaves me with an engine that still runs with the smaller screw turned all the
> way in. Anyone know a base setting for both the screws in question?
